{"content": "Given:\n\n\\[\nf(x) = x^7 + a x^3 + c x\n\\]\n\\[\nf(5) = 3\n\\]\n\nWe are to find \\( f(-5) \\).\n\n---\n\nCalculate \\( f(5) \\):\n\n\\[\nf(5) = 5^7 + a(5^3) + c(5) = 3\n\\]\n\\[\nf(5) = 78125 + 125a + 5c = 3\n\\]\n\n---\n\nCalculate \\( f(-5) \\):\n\n\\[\nf(-5) = (-5)^7 + a(-5)^3 + c(-5)\n\\]\n\\[\n(-5)^7 = -78125\n\\]\n\\[\n(-5)^3 = -125\n\\]\nSo,\n\\[\nf(-5) = -78125 + a(-125) + c(-5) = -78125 - 125a - 5c\n\\]\n\n---\n\nNow, add \\( f(5) \\) and \\( f(-5) \\):\n\n\\[\nf(5) = 78125 + 125a + 5c\n\\]\n\\[\nf(-5) = -78125 - 125a - 5c\n\\]\n\\[\nf(5) + f(-5) = (78125 - 78125) + (125a - 125a) + (5c - 5c", "in": 61, "out": 300}